1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:18,000
When AI work spans multiple conversations, past information, current state, confirmed decisions, and ideas can easily become mixed. LOGOS Continuity is an approval-gated continuity tool designed to prevent that failure.

2
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Codex accelerated the state architecture, API, React interface, safety rules, 54 automated tests, browser QA, and public deployment.

3
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Instead of merely remembering everything, Command Center ranks the most urgent continuity risks and routes the user to the correct resolution workflow.

4
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:20,000
In a new session, GPT-5.6 identifies the intended project from natural language. LOGOS restores verified truth, current state, next actions, and unverified checkpoint warnings as separate layers.

5
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:43,000
GPT-5.6 classifies the statement into a structured state, but it cannot directly change canonical truth. An uncertain idea remains in Exploration until the user explicitly approves a change.

6
00:01:43,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Conflicting claims never silently overwrite canonical state. The user can keep the existing decision, apply a temporary exception, or approve a new canonical decision.

7
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Current state, next actions, exploration, and recovery checkpoints remain operationally separate. Every commit and conflict resolution preserves the before state, after state, reason, and provenance.

8
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:48,000
The next session receives an authority-ordered continuity layer rather than an unverified memory dump.

9
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:55,000
LOGOS turns long-running AI work from probabilistic recall into approval-gated, provenance-aware continuity.
